<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-25T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/5–2545: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-25T20:00:00-04:00">May 25,
                                    1945—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1145. Please inform FonOff that at 4 a.m. May 24 Agrarian leader G. M.
                            Dimitrov sought asylum at the residence in Sofia of the United States
                            Representative in Bulgaria, who forthwith placed the matter before the
                            Bulgarian authorities. The Department has approved Barnes’ action and
                            instructed him to seek assurances that appropriate measures be taken to
                            ensure Dimitrov’s safety.</p>
                        <p>This instruction is being sent to Moscow and London;<note n="59" xml:id="d207fn1">As No. 4166 to London.</note> repeated to
                                Sofia.<note n="60" xml:id="d207fn2">As No. 145.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>